  <h2>What cookies are</h2>
  <p>Cookies are small text files that websites place on your device to remember information about you and your visit. They are widely used to make websites work, improve user experience and provide analytics about how a site is used.</p>

  <h2>Cookies currently used on this site</h2>
  <p>This website (gemini.ampm.co.uk) does <strong>not</strong> currently set any first-party cookies and does not run third-party analytics, advertising or marketing tracking.</p>
  <p>The website is served via Cloudflare, which may set strictly-necessary security cookies (for example <code>__cf_bm</code> for bot detection) for the security of the connection. These are essential for the site to operate safely and do not require user consent under PECR / the UK GDPR.</p>

  <h2>If you submit a form</h2>
  <p>Our contact and enquiry forms are processed by the third-party service <a href="https://formsubmit.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Formsubmit.co</a>, which forwards your submission to our email. Formsubmit applies its own cookies on the form-submission redirect page; please refer to its own privacy notice for details.</p>

  <h2>Future tracking</h2>
  <p>If we add analytics or marketing tracking (for example Google Analytics 4, Microsoft Clarity, or LinkedIn Insight) in future, we will update this policy and present a consent banner before any non-essential cookies are set, in line with PECR and the UK GDPR.</p>

  <h2>How to control cookies</h2>
  <p>Most browsers let you view, manage and delete cookies in their settings. The Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office maintains plain-English guidance at <a href="https://ico.org.uk/your-data-matters/online/cookies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk/your-data-matters/online/cookies/</a>.</p>
</Legal>
